  "title": "Mary Colter's Lookout Sudio - Grand Canyon National Park (U.S. National Park Service)",
  "html": "<body class=\"ParkSite\"><span aria-label=\"Top of page\" id=\"__topdoc__\" role=\"navigation\"></span>\n\n<!--googleoff: index-->\n<div id=\"beforeSkipLinks\" tabindex=\"-1\"></div>\n\n<!--googleon: index-->\n<!--googleoff: index-->\n\n<!--googleon: index-->\n<!--googleoff: index-->\n<div class=\"GlobalHeader usaGlobalHeader\" role=\"banner\">\n\n</div>\n<!--googleon: index-->\n<div aria-hidden=\"true\" aria-labelledby=\"exitModalLabel\" class=\"modal refreshableModal\" id=\"myModal\" tabindex=\"-1\">\n<div class=\"modal-dialog\">\n<div class=\"modal-content\">\n<div class=\"modal-header\">\n<h2 class=\"modal-title visually-hidden\" id=\"exitModalLabel\">Exiting nps.gov</h2>\n<button aria-label=\"Close\" class=\"btn-close\" data-bs-dismiss=\"modal\" type=\"button\"></button>\n</div>\n<div class=\"modal-body\"></div>\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_Schedule\" id=\"cs_control_481716\"><div id=\"CS_Element_BannerContainer\" title=\"\"><div class=\"cs_GridRow\" id=\"gridRow_1_1_481716\"><div class=\"cs_GridColumn\" id=\"gridCol_1_1_1_1_481716\"><div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_CustomCF\" id=\"cs_control_830326\"><div id=\"CS_CCF_2043147_830326\">\n\n</div></div><div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_CustomCF\" id=\"cs_control_481855\"><div id=\"CS_CCF_2043147_481855\"> </div></div></div></div></div></div>\n<div id=\"Park-header\">\n<div class=\"container\">\n<div class=\"pull-left\">\n<!--googleoff: index-->\n\n<!--googleon: index-->\n\n</div>\n<!--googleoff: index-->\n\n<!--googleon: index-->\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"container\">\n<div aria-label=\"Alerts Notification\" class=\"AlertsNotification\" data-site-code=\"grca\" id=\"AlertsNotification\" role=\"dialog\">\n<div aria-live=\"polite\" class=\"AlertsNotification__Status visually-hidden\" role=\"status\">Loading alerts</div>\n<div class=\"collapse\">\n<div class=\"AlertsNotification__Panel\">\n<div class=\"AlertsNotification__Header\">\n<h2 class=\"Tag\" id=\"AlertsNotificationHeading\">Alerts In Effect</h2>\n<button aria-label=\"Dismiss\" class=\"AlertsNotification__DismissButton\" type=\"button\">\nDismiss\n<svg class=\"usa-icon\" focusable=\"false\" role=\"presentation\">\n<use href=\"/theme/assets/vendor/npsds/packages/icons/dist/sprite.svg#close\"></use>\n</svg>\n</button>\n<span class=\"hr clearfix\"></span>\n</div>\n<div class=\"AlertsNotification__Body\" id=\"AlertsNotificationBody\">\n<div class=\"AlertsNotification__MoreLinkContainer\">\n<svg class=\"usa-icon\" focusable=\"false\" role=\"presentation\">\n<use href=\"/theme/assets/vendor/npsds/packages/icons/dist/sprite.svg#add\"></use>\n</svg>\n<a class=\"AlertsNotification__MoreLink\" href=\"/grca/planyourvisit/conditions.htm\" id=\"AlertsNotificationMoreLink\" tabindex=\"-1\">\nmore information on current conditions...\n</a>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"MainContent\" id=\"main\" role=\"main\">\n\n<div aria-labelledby=\"modal-contact-us-label\" class=\"modal fade\" id=\"modal-contact-us\" tabindex=\"-1\">\n<div class=\"modal-dialog\">\n<div class=\"modal-content\">\n<div class=\"modal-header\">\n<h4 class=\"modal-title visually-hidden\" id=\"modal-contact-us-label\">Contact Us</h4>\n<button aria-label=\"Close\" class=\"btn-close\" data-bs-dismiss=\"modal\" type=\"button\"></button>\n</div>\n<div class=\"modal-body\">\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div id=\"adminTools\"></div>\n<div class=\"container\">\n<div class=\"ColumnGrid row\">\n<!--googleoff: index-->\n<div class=\"container\">\n\n</div>\n<!--googleon: index-->\n<div class=\"ColumnMain col-sm-12\">\n<div class=\"ContentHeader text-content-size\">\n<h1 class=\"page-title\">Mary Colter's Lookout Sudio</h1>\n</div>\n<div class=\"row\">\n<div class=\"col-sm-12\">\n<div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_Layout\" id=\"cs_control_2\"><table cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"CS_Layout_Table\" id=\"cs_idLayout2\" summary=\"\" width=\"100%\"><tr class=\"CS_Layout_TR\"><td class=\"CS_Layout_TD\" id=\"cs_idCell2x1x1\">\n<div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_Custom\" id=\"cs_control_5504802\">\n<div class=\"Component ArticleTextGroup TextWrapped clearfix\">\n<figure class=\"-auto-width\">\n<picture>\n<source srcset=\"/grca/learn/photosmultimedia/images/Lookout-Studio-Banner_1.jpg?maxwidth=1300&amp;autorotate=false&amp;quality=78&amp;format=webp\" type=\"image/webp\"/>\n<img alt=\"A historic image of Lookout Studio on the left and a modern image of Lookout Studio on the right.\" src=\"/grca/learn/photosmultimedia/images/Lookout-Studio-Banner_1.jpg?maxwidth=1300&amp;autorotate=false\" title=\"\"/>\n</picture>\n</figure><!-- floating-image alignment  -->\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"CS_Layout_SpacingHeight\" id=\"cs_spacer_2043152\" style=\"line-height:1;\"> </div>\n<div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_Custom\" id=\"cs_control_2043152\">\n<div class=\"Component ArticleTextGroup TextWrapped clearfix\">\n<strong>Lookout Studio (1914)</strong> was designed as a location where visitors could photograph the Grand Canyon from its precipitous edge and use the telescopes to observe the natural beauty the canyon offered. Built on a precipice west of El Tovar, \"The Lookout\" offered a neat, comfortable rustic studio of stone and log timbers.<br/>\n<br/>\nColter designed the exterior stonework to convey an indigenous American Indian structure, similar to the ruins of the Ancestral Puebloan dwellings found in the region. Here, she allowed the edge of the canyon and the natural rock outcroppings give form to her multi-level structure that grew out of the edge of the rim.<br/>\n<br/>\nInspired by the natural forms of the landscape around the site, the parapet rooflines and stone chimneys mimicked the irregular shapes of surrounding bedrock. The interior of the building is divided into several levels, with structural logwork exposed in posts, beams, and ceiling joists. The floor is scored concrete and the interior walls are exposed stone. Because of all of the viewing windows around the walls of the structure, the interior is considerably lighter than most of Colter's other buildings.\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"CS_Layout_SpacingHeight\" id=\"cs_spacer_5511458\" style=\"line-height:1;\"> </div>\n<div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_Custom\" id=\"cs_control_5511458\">\n<div class=\"Component ArticleTextGroup TextWrapped clearfix\">\n<figure class=\"-left\">\n<picture>\n<source srcset=\"/grca/learn/historyculture/images/Lookout-Studio-Historic.jpg?maxwidth=650&amp;autorotate=false&amp;quality=78&amp;format=webp\" type=\"image/webp\"/>\n<img alt=\"A black and white photo of the Lookout Studio.\" src=\"/grca/learn/historyculture/images/Lookout-Studio-Historic.jpg?maxwidth=650&amp;autorotate=false\" title=\"Lookout Studio Historic Photo\"/>\n</picture>\n<figcaption>Lookout Studio in 1914. </figcaption>\n</figure><!-- floating-image alignment  -->\n<p>When designing Lookout Studio, Colter allowed the surrounding landscape to guide her design. The native stone structure, originally known as \"the Lookout,\" is built into the canyon rim and, in a sense, looks as if it grows out of it. The small structure is generally rectangular in plan and constructed of coursed rubble masonry. The uneven parapet of part of the roof steps up to incorporate the chimney and a small observation room within its lines.<br/>\n<br/>\nThe observation room has a small balcony with a jigsaw-patterned railing. Low stone walls lead up to the building, protecting visitors from drop offs into the canyon. </p>\n<p>The interior of the structure is divided into several levels. Structural logwork is exposed on the interior (posts, beams, and ceiling joists) and a small stone fireplace provides the simpler atmosphere Colter achieved here. The floor is scored concrete. Interior walls are exposed stone. Because of all of the viewing windows around the walls of the structure, the interior is considerably lighter than most other Colter buildings. A small stairway with log newel posts and railings leads up into the small enclosed observation tower and down from the building's main level to an exit that opens to an exterior observation area.<br/>\n<br/>\nThe original ceiling treatment, probably latias (saplings), has been covered over although the vigas remain exposed. The ceiling finish is now sheetrock or a similar material. Fluorescent lights, another alteration to the building, provide additional lighting on the interior. The building has undergone little alteration, other than those changes listed above.</p>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"CS_Layout_SpacingHeight\" id=\"cs_spacer_5504801\" style=\"line-height:1;\"> </div>\n<div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_Custom\" id=\"cs_control_5504801\">\n<div class=\"Component FeatureGrid\">\n<div class=\"row\">\n<div class=\"FeatureGrid-item col-sm-6\">\n<div class=\"Component Feature -medium\">\n<a class=\"Feature-link\" href=\"https://www.flickr.com/photos/grand_canyon_nps/albums/72157627107171930/\" onclick=\"gas('send', 'event', 'Feature Grid - Prioritized', document.location.href, 'https://www.flickr.com/photos/grand_canyon_nps/albums/72157627107171930/', 1, true)\">\n<div class=\"Feature-imageContainer\">\n<img alt=\"Photo of Lookout Studio\" class=\"Feature-image\" sizes=\"(min-width: 1380px) 640px, (min-width: 1200px) 550px, (min-width: 576px) 50vw, 100vw\" src=\"/common/uploads/grid_builder/grca/crop16_9/79A70AB2-1DD8-B71B-0BD83E1F41502C87.jpg?width=640&amp;quality=90&amp;mode=crop\" srcset=\"/common/uploads/grid_builder/grca/crop16_9/79A70AB2-1DD8-B71B-0BD83E1F41502C87.jpg?width=420&amp;quality=90&amp;mode=crop 420w, /common/uploads/grid_builder/grca/crop16_9/79A70AB2-1DD8-B71B-0BD83E1F41502C87.jpg?width=640&amp;quality=90&amp;mode=crop 640w\"/>\n<div class=\"Feature-title carrot-end\">Lookout Studio (1914)</div>\n</div>\n</a>\n<p class=\"Feature-description\">Continue to Lookout Studio photo gallery on Flickr</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"FeatureGrid-item col-sm-6\">\n<div class=\"Component Feature -medium\">\n<a class=\"Feature-link\" href=\"http://grcahistory.org/sites/south-rim/lookout-studio/\" onclick=\"gas('send', 'event', 'Feature Grid - Prioritized', document.location.href, 'http://grcahistory.org/sites/south-rim/lookout-studio/', 1, true)\">\n<div class=\"Feature-imageContainer\">\n<img alt=\"A stone building on the edge of the canyon at sunset.\" class=\"Feature-image\" sizes=\"(min-width: 1380px) 640px, (min-width: 1200px) 550px, (min-width: 576px) 50vw, 100vw\" src=\"/common/uploads/grid_builder/grca/crop16_9/1BD639B5-CF9F-43AF-CFF804E1CE0293E4.jpg?width=640&amp;quality=90&amp;mode=crop\" srcset=\"/common/uploads/grid_builder/grca/crop16_9/1BD639B5-CF9F-43AF-CFF804E1CE0293E4.jpg?width=420&amp;quality=90&amp;mode=crop 420w, /common/uploads/grid_builder/grca/crop16_9/1BD639B5-CF9F-43AF-CFF804E1CE0293E4.jpg?width=640&amp;quality=90&amp;mode=crop 640w\"/>\n<div class=\"Feature-title carrot-end\">Lookout Studio History Continued</div>\n</div>\n</a>\n<p class=\"Feature-description\">Learn more about Lookout Studio on Arizona State University's Nature, Culture, and History at Grand Canyon website.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"row\">\n<div class=\"FeatureGrid-item col-sm-4\">\n<div class=\"Component Feature -small\">\n<a class=\"Feature-link\" href=\"/grca/learn/historyculture/historic-village.htm\" onclick=\"gas('send', 'event', 'Feature Grid - Prioritized', document.location.href, '/grca/learn/historyculture/historic-village.htm', 1, true)\">\n<div class=\"Feature-imageContainer\">\n<img alt=\"The side of the Grand Canyon in the snow.\" class=\"Feature-image\" sizes=\"(min-width: 1380px) 420px, (min-width: 1200px) 360px, (min-width: 576px) 33vw, 100vw\" src=\"/common/uploads/grid_builder/grca/crop16_9/594BFA1F-D914-9667-56FF83C36A125878.jpg?width=640&amp;quality=90&amp;mode=crop\" srcset=\"/common/uploads/grid_builder/grca/crop16_9/594BFA1F-D914-9667-56FF83C36A125878.jpg?width=420&amp;quality=90&amp;mode=crop 420w, /common/uploads/grid_builder/grca/crop16_9/594BFA1F-D914-9667-56FF83C36A125878.jpg?width=640&amp;quality=90&amp;mode=crop 640w\"/>\n<div class=\"Feature-title carrot-end\">The Historic Village</div>\n</div>\n</a>\n<p class=\"Feature-description\">With the arrival of the First Steam-Powered Train in 1901, the quiet area of the South Rim rapidly expanded into the Grand Canyon Village.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"FeatureGrid-item col-sm-4\">\n<div class=\"Component Feature -small\">\n<a class=\"Feature-link\" href=\"/grca/learn/photosmultimedia/colter_index.htm\" onclick=\"gas('send', 'event', 'Feature Grid - Prioritized', document.location.href, '/grca/learn/photosmultimedia/colter_index.htm', 1, true)\">\n<div class=\"Feature-imageContainer\">\n<img alt=\"A black and white photo of a women sitting in a chair.\" class=\"Feature-image\" sizes=\"(min-width: 1380px) 420px, (min-width: 1200px) 360px, (min-width: 576px) 33vw, 100vw\" src=\"/common/uploads/grid_builder/grca/crop16_9/58F5DD3C-C0A4-2B97-0170156EBE20185C.jpg?width=640&amp;quality=90&amp;mode=crop\" srcset=\"/common/uploads/grid_builder/grca/crop16_9/58F5DD3C-C0A4-2B97-0170156EBE20185C.jpg?width=420&amp;quality=90&amp;mode=crop 420w, /common/uploads/grid_builder/grca/crop16_9/58F5DD3C-C0A4-2B97-0170156EBE20185C.jpg?width=640&amp;quality=90&amp;mode=crop 640w\"/>\n<div class=\"Feature-title carrot-end\">Mary Colter's Buildings</div>\n</div>\n</a>\n<p class=\"Feature-description\">Mary Colter was the chief architect and decorator for the Fred Harvey Company from 1902 to 1948.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"FeatureGrid-item col-sm-4\">\n<div class=\"Component Feature -small\">\n<a class=\"Feature-link\" href=\"/grca/learn/historyculture/entrepeneurs.htm\" onclick=\"gas('send', 'event', 'Feature Grid - Prioritized', document.location.href, '/grca/learn/historyculture/entrepeneurs.htm', 1, true)\">\n<div class=\"Feature-imageContainer\">\n<img alt=\"John Verkamp in front of his tent.\" class=\"Feature-image\" sizes=\"(min-width: 1380px) 420px, (min-width: 1200px) 360px, (min-width: 576px) 33vw, 100vw\" src=\"/common/uploads/grid_builder/grca/crop16_9/214B190F-0E07-4A2C-2BD4BE784547DC36.jpg?width=640&amp;quality=90&amp;mode=crop\" srcset=\"/common/uploads/grid_builder/grca/crop16_9/214B190F-0E07-4A2C-2BD4BE784547DC36.jpg?width=420&amp;quality=90&amp;mode=crop 420w, /common/uploads/grid_builder/grca/crop16_9/214B190F-0E07-4A2C-2BD4BE784547DC36.jpg?width=640&amp;quality=90&amp;mode=crop 640w\"/>\n<div class=\"Feature-title carrot-end\">Entrepreneurs</div>\n</div>\n</a>\n<p class=\"Feature-description\">After the Santa Fe Railroad started bringing visitors to the canyon, entrepreneurs came to the canyon to make their fortune.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</td></tr>\n</table></div>\n</div><!-- col-sm-12 -->\n</div><!-- row -->\n</div><!-- ColumnMain col-sm-9 -->\n</div><!-- ColumnGrid row -->\n</div><!-- end container -->\n<div class=\"container\">\n<div class=\"ColumnGrid row\">\n<div class=\"ColumnMain col-sm-12\">\n<div class=\"row\">\n<div class=\"col-sm-12 text-content-size text-content-style\">\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\">Last updated: September 21, 2019</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<!--googleoff: index-->\n <!-- ParkFooter -->\n<!--googleon: index-->\n\n</div><!-- end of <div main> -->\n<!--googleoff: index-->\n\n<!--googleon: index-->\n<!-- the rest of the scripts are leftovers from before the centennial down and should be pared down where possible -->\n\n<link href=\"/common/commonspot/templates/assets/libs/colorbox/colorbox.css\" rel=\"stylesheet\"/>\n\n<div class=\"modal fade\" id=\"outdated-browser\" role=\"dialog\" tabindex=\"-1\">\n</div>\n</body>",
